The paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves introducing an auxiliary variable to improve the performance of existing approaches, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the limitations of current methods and proposes a new solution, which involves modeling one-to-many mappings and decoupling the relevance of generators, both of which are topics in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
